{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Re-home CLAUDE.md-native content into authoritative docs\n\n## Why\n\nSlimming the root guidance file (S2) requires the content it currently owns to have an\nauthoritative home in `docs/` first, so nothing is lost. A grounded read of `docs/` shows only\nthe `idea` status is genuinely unhomed today; the parent-first cascade already lives in\n`docs/concurrency.md` I4a, and the linking/tags/session-log write-level mechanics already live\nin `docs/event-schema.md`. The real gap is one **agent-facing conceptual home** for the ticket\nmodel.\n\n## What\n\n- Create **`docs/ticket-model.md`** holding the *agent-facing concept* for four topics: the\n  `idea` status lifecycle (its dispatch/gate/`validate` semantics), hierarchy/containment\n  (`parent_id`, not a link relation), linking (the six relations + the promotion *concept*), and\n  the tags surface + the `--set-tags` add-wins convergence caveat. Cross-reference\n  `docs/event-schema.md` for the write-level event mechanics (CREATE genesis, LINK/UNLINK,\n  TAG_DELTA) — **do not restate event bodies** (drift risk).\n- Fold CLAUDE.md's cascade **gate-interaction** paragraph (a cascaded parent claim runs the\n  parent's own plan-review gate; epics/stories are not gate-exempt; `--force` propagates) into\n  `docs/concurrency.md` I4a, which already documents the cascade itself.\n- Add a `## The session_log ticket type` section to `docs/event-schema.md` (promote the existing\n  CREATE-row note into a real section); keep the session-log **capture helper + auto-rotation**\n  in `docs/user-guide.md`, cross-referencing `docs/config.md` for the fingerprint resolver.\n- Index `docs/ticket-model.md` in `docs/README.md`.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `docs/ticket-model.md` (new) and `docs/{event-schema,concurrency,user-guide,README}.md`.\nOut: editing `CLAUDE.md` (that is S2, which replaces these sections with pointers) and any code\nchange. This story is docs-only.\n\n## Design decisions (spike-validated)\n\nThe original \"five topics with no backing doc\" premise was partly wrong (confirmed by a grounded\ndocs read). Only `idea` is unhomed; the cascade and the linking/tags/session-log write mechanics\nalready have authoritative homes, so `docs/ticket-model.md` carries the *concept* + cross-refs,\nnot duplicated event bodies. This keeps a single source of truth and avoids doc drift.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `docs/ticket-model.md` exists and documents all four concept topics (idea status,\n  hierarchy/containment, linking relations+promotion, tags surface + `--set-tags` caveat).\n  - Proving: `test -f docs/ticket-model.md && rg -c 'idea|parent_id|discovered_from|set-tags' docs/ticket-model.md` (≥ 4 matches)\n- [ ] `docs/ticket-model.md` cross-references `docs/event-schema.md` and does not restate event\n  bodies.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'event-schema' docs/ticket-model.md` (≥ 1 match)\n- [ ] `docs/concurrency.md` I4a gains the cascade gate-interaction nuance.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'gate-exempt|plan-review|--force' docs/concurrency.md` (≥ 1 match)\n- [ ] `docs/event-schema.md` gains a `## The session_log ticket type` section.\n  - Proving: `rg -n '## The session_log ticket type' docs/event-schema.md`\n- [ ] `docs/user-guide.md` retains the session-log capture-helper section.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'session-log append|append_session_log' docs/user-guide.md`\n- [ ] `docs/README.md` indexes `docs/ticket-model.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'ticket-model' docs/README.md`\n- [ ] `make lint` passes.\n  - Proving: `make lint`"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784234386166738001,"uuid":"3010e343-c21c-4c14-a798-38d2428e45d9"}